The paper deals with private information retrieval, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses colluding servers, which is a security issue (cs.CR). The use of MDS coded databases and distributed storage systems suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and computer communication (cs.CC). Finally, the paper's focus on applications and practical implementation may make it relevant to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SI).
